channel.title: How to change cache/zip cache etc
channel.description:
[center]Difficulty: Easy 1/10 Tested on: Project dungeonfest client and project ecko client Knowledge: Basic java knowledge As requested by Austin Cadle, I'm posting this tut on how to change the cache revision and the link in the cache downloader.
This is if you were using a cache decoder: Step 1: Lets say I zipped my 666 cache all over again, this is what you do.
[IMG]http://i56.tinypic.com/317k2tx.jpg[/img]
Step 2: Next do this: use this format: [b].(what you wanna name it)_cache [/b]
[IMG]http://i52.tinypic.com/oa0p47.jpg[/img]
[b]Make sure it's .zip (as you would know)[/b]
Step 3: Then comes the fun part!!!!!!
[img]http://i51.tinypic.com/68vlvd.png[/img]
option 1: Download drop box, then go to the folder and do this with the zipped file:
[img]http://i56.tinypic.com/qpmb60.png[/img]
Then wait till its done and copy paste the link/replace the link to/in your client, change the revision, and change the name of what it used to be called and you should be good to go.
Here's an example I put together(with a 562 loading 663 cache)(clientsettings.java): Before: [code=java]public class ClientSettings {
public static String getCacheDir() { return System.getProperty("user.home") + ".derbyscapev3_cache"; //only change this if you edit cache } public static final String cacheLink = "http://dl.dropbox.com/u/39980951/Matrix/cache5.zip"; //make sure it zip public static final int cacheRevision = 5; //change this if you edit cache
public static final String ip = "Your IP"; public static final int port = 43594; public static final String background_music_name = "Scape Original"; //rs classic music <3 public static final String serverName = "DerbyScape"; //server name, also auto changes client title and load bar public static final String websiteLink = "Website link here(for your website [u][b]NOT[/b][/u] cache)"; //so it goes ur website instead of rs, example on acc creation terms service button public static final Color startLoadClientBackgroundColor = Color.black; //Color.black default public static final boolean disable_server_list = true; //dont disable this :D, ofc you may but then serverlist doesnt work anymore public static final boolean disable_ukeys_check = true; //containers table information check but ppl give weird names for stuff as: "ukeys" public static final boolean disable_keys_request = false; //if this true, disable_ukeys_check has to be true too, when this true, you can load client without connecting server
[/code]
After: [code=java]public class ClientSettings {
public static String getCacheDir() { return System.getProperty("user.home") + ".derbyscapev4_cache"; //[b]only change this if you edit cache[/b] } public static final String cacheLink = "http://dl.dropbox.com/u/38224169/.rspscache_cache.zip"; //make sure it zip public static final int cacheRevision = 6; //[b]change this if you edit cache[/b]
public static final String ip = "Your IP"; public static final int port = 43594; public static final String background_music_name = "Scape Original"; //rs classic music <3 public static final String serverName = "DerbyScape"; //server name, also auto changes client title and load bar public static final String websiteLink = "Website link here(for your website [u][b]NOT[/b][/u] cache)"; //so it goes ur website instead of rs, example on acc creation terms service button public static final Color startLoadClientBackgroundColor = Color.black; //Color.black default public static final boolean disable_server_list = true; //dont disable this :D, ofc you may but then serverlist doesnt work anymore public static final boolean disable_ukeys_check = true; //containers table information check but ppl give weird names for stuff as: "ukeys" public static final boolean disable_keys_request = false; //if this true, disable_ukeys_check has to be true too, when this true, you can load client without connecting server
[/code]
Now onto lets say you have cache link, but you just want to change the cache:
Change this:
[code=java]public class ClientSettings {
public static String getCacheDir() { return System.getProperty("user.home") + "your cache name"; //only change this if you edit cache } public static final String cacheLink = "previous cache link"; //make sure it zip public static final int cacheRevision = 5; //change this if you edit cache [/code]
To this:
[code=java]public class ClientSettings {
public static String getCacheDir() { return System.getProperty("user.home") + "what you wanna call it"; //only change this if you edit cache } public static final String cacheLink = "The link you got"; //make sure it zip public static final int cacheRevision = 5; //change this to the next number. [/code]
Now an example for 317s (this is from project ecko): You should find this in client.java This code: [code=java5] drawLoadingText(15, "Downloading Cache"); String url = "cache link here(needs to have .zip at the end)"; if (Math.random() > 0.5) { url = "cache link here(needs to have .zip at the end)"; System.out.println("Project Ecko");[/code]
Now just replace The cache links with the link you found, save, compile, then run.
I hope this helped.
Because some noobs might copy and paste this on rune-serv3R or rUn3-L0cUs. I've made a little rule:
This was made by me and can't be re-posted/posted by anyone but me or people that I give permission to. If caught I will request a moderator lock they're post/remove it.
[u][b]I only give permission of re-posting this onto other communities to these people:[/b][/u]
Permission list:
[ul][li]Austin Cadle [/li] [li]I Roll Deep[/li][/ul]
Credits:
Me (judostar/slayerjj)
The cache decoder's creator.[/center]
